\begin{multicols}{2} % Two-column layout throughout the main article text

\section{Kinds of wastes}
\begin{itemize}
    \item solid $\Leftrightarrow$ liquid
    \item bio-degradable $\Leftrightarrow$ non-biodegradable
    \item hazardous $\Leftrightarrow$ non-hazardous
\end{itemize}
  $\hookrightarrow$ different methods of disposal

\section{Effects of waste if not managed wisely}
Affects our health, socio-economic conditions, coastal and marine environment, climate
and aesthetics

\section{Most used methods of disposal}
\textbf{Landfill}: dispose of waste material by burying it and covering it over with soil, esp. as a method of filling in or extending usable land. \\ \newline
\textbf{Incineration}: controlled burning of waste in a furnace at high temperatures.

\section{What can I do?}
You could: Purchase products in bulk, Use durable towels, tablecloths, napkins, dishes, cups, and glasses, donate or exchange old books, clothes, ..
\end{multicols}

